      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "moat-text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 440,
      "y": 490,
      "width": 330,
      "height": 90,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 82,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 82,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 0,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The moat isn't just the AI — it's what the AI learns:\n\n① Community failure patterns → more users = smarter playbooks\n   → Classic network effect (like Waze for ops)\n\n② Integration depth (Prometheus, Grafana, k8s, PagerDuty)\n   → Harder to rip out than to adopt\n\n③ Our domain fluency — we already speak SRE, chaos,\n   resilience. Incumbents don't.\n\n④ Worldline as design partner + first reference customer",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 10
    },

    {
